<p><span data-path-to-node="4,10,1,0"><strong>Indoors</strong></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,11,1,0">– this year, {music} activities are popular</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,12,1,0">– they hear a {story} everyday</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,13,0,0"><strong>Fees:</strong></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,13,1,0">Now costs $ {470} per term</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,14,1,0">Fees include:</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,15,1,0">– a trip to a {farm} this year</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,16,1,0">– chance to take home a {toy} every week</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 80.8px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,17,0,0"><strong>Do not forget:</strong></span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,17,1,0">– Put a {pillow} in Suzie’s bag</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.2px;">
<td style="width: 17.6038%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
<td style="width: 77.127%; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span data-path-to-node="4,18,1,0">– Arrange a visit; phone number: {0914638520}</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a telephone conversation between a man who’s finding out about a preschool for his young daughter and a woman who works there. First you have some time to look at questions 1 to 5 on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. Now listen carefully and answer questions 1 to five.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>Woman (Sally):</strong> Good morning, Riverdale Preschool, Sally speaking.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong>Man (Robert):</strong> Hello, my name is Robert. I’ve got a four year old daughter called Susie and I’d like to get some information about your preschool please.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Sure Robert. Well Susie’s the right age. We take three and four year olds in classes of <strong>20</strong> students.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Robert:</strong>  Oh great. And how many teachers do you have?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Sally:</strong> We have two, the first group is taught by Mrs Oliver and the second group is taken by Mrs <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(1) KEOgH</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Robert :</strong>Just a moment, I’ll write that down. Could you spell the last name please? It’s an unusual one, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Sally:</strong>Yes, it’s K-E-O-G-H.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Robert :</strong> Okay, I’ve got that now.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>Robert:</strong> I know the children attend for two or three days a week. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong>Sally:</strong>That’s right. The older ones like Susie are here for three days, which means <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) 15</strong> </span>hours a week. The younger ones, the three year olds, attend two days a week, that’s a total of 10 hours.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>Robert:</strong> And what do they do during that time?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well half the day is spent outside and the children can run around and play games with their friends or do a calmer activity like painting for example. We have a great outside play area that we’re improving all the time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> Yes, we were walking past the other day and Susie noticed you&#8217;ve recently put in a new slide, haven&#8217;t you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sally:</strong> Yes, we&#8217;re really pleased with it. It’s a big one and the children love it</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> And are you thinking of adding anything else outdoors?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sally:</strong>Well we were hoping to build a playhouse, but that was too expensive, so we’re now making plans for a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(3) garden</strong> </span>where the children will be able to grow flowers and vegetables. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong>Robert:</strong>Lovely. And what else do the children do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well the other half of the day is spent indoors. This year, the children seem to be very interested in <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(4) music</strong></span>, so the teachers are doing a lot of activities related to that.Last year, there seemed to be more of an interest in dancing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> Well, Susie would love either of those.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sally:</strong>The teachers may sometimes play quiet games with the children, but we always make time for a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(5) story</strong></span> each day. It’s a very important part of the program here.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> Yes, of course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 6 to 10 on page two. Now listen and answer questions 6 to ten.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong>Robert:</strong> Now I’d like to ask you about the fees, if that’s okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Sure. We actually had to put them up this term, I’m afraid. I heard from a friend of mine that it used to be $420 for the term, but it’s just gone up to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(6)</strong> $<strong>470</strong></span>. Is that right? Yes, we had to add the extra $<strong>50</strong> to cover costs.Things got a lot more expensive last year. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> Hmm, I understand. And I think the fees are still quite reasonable. Another school I&#8217;ve spoken to charges $500 per term.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sally:</strong> Oh really?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong>Robert:</strong> My friend also told me that his daughter went on a trip to the local zoo and that the cost of that was covered in the fees. Is that right?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Yes, we did that last year, but we’ll be going to a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) farm</strong></span> this year instead. We vary it; so for example, we may go to the theatre next year.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> Okay, it sounds like fun.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong>Sally:</strong>Also included in the price is membership of a special library. Children can borrow a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(8) toy</strong></span> and keep it for a week and choose a different one the following week. It’s very popular.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> What a great idea! We would certainly make use of that system if we enroll. Now is there anything else I should know?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well, the children have a rest here during the day and we make up a little bed for them with sheets and blankets, but we advise parents to pack a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(9) pillow</strong></span> in the child’s bag as we don’t provide one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Robert:</strong> Okay, I’ll make a note of that. So what should I do if I want to come and look around the school during the day and meet the staff?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong>Sally:</strong>The best thing is to call the teacher on the classroom mobile and she’ll tell you which time is best to visit. Shall I give you the number?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong>Robert:</strong>Yes, please.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong>Sally:</strong>Okay, it’s <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) 0914638520</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong>Robert:</strong> Thanks for all your help Sally and we hope to see you soon.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong>Sally:</strong> No problem, bye for now.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 1. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fcc3f77e-a2b2-426d-b96c-617d73a36358', 'b4e3507e-d022-4952-bbbd-edb2e33529c6', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C, or D.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter in boxes 27-31 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "It started earlier than previously thought."}, {"content": "Historians have overlooked its importance."}, {"content": "It impacts on research into the wider region."}, {"content": "Researchers have calculated its effects on the environment."}], "question": "In the first paragraph, what is the writer''s main point about migration to Patagonia?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "to challenge previous research"}, {"content": "to propose new areas to investigate"}, {"content": "to summarise a scholarly debate"}, {"content": "to suggest reasons for human migration"}], "question": "In the second paragraph, what is the writer''s purpose?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "compare it with another theory of migration."}, {"content": "evaluate the success of American migration."}, {"content": "criticise the speed of research into migration."}, {"content": "compare migration in different parts of the world."}], "question": "The writer refers to the \"late\" model in order to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "Scholars support the idea of fast migrations."}, {"content": "It is too random to be a convincing theory."}, {"content": "South America was more habitable at an earlier time."}, {"content": "South America was more habitable at an earlier time."}], "question": "What is the writer''s main point about the \"early model\"?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "It is much younger than researchers once estimated."}, {"content": "It provides supporting evidence for relatively early settlement."}, {"content": "Archaeologists believe the site is of questionable value."}, {"content": "Streams exposed the site, making new research possible."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about the Monte Verde site?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">27. In the first paragraph, what is the writer’s main point about migration to Patagonia?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">C. It impacts on research into the wider region.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 1) “The earliest occupation of Patagonia carries </span><strong class=\"\">obvious implications for understanding when the North and South American continents were peopled</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> because it gives a </span><strong class=\"\">baseline</strong><span class=\"\"> that all calculations…</span><span class=\"\"> must take into account.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng việc nghiên cứu sự định cư sớm nhất ở Patagonia cung cấp một “baseline” (mốc cơ sở) quan trọng.</span><span class=\"\"> Mốc này giúp các nhà khoa học hiểu được toàn bộ quá trình con người di cư đến Bắc và Nam Mỹ (vùng rộng lớn hơn – </span><em class=\"\">wider region</em><span class=\"\">).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">28. In the second paragraph, what is the writer’s purpose?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">C. to summarise a scholarly debate.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) “However,</span> <strong class=\"\">fundamental disagreements developed</strong><span class=\"\"> concerning the length of time involved…</span><span class=\"\"> and the </span><strong class=\"\">debate is still with us today</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Mục đích của đoạn 2 là giới thiệu về sự bất đồng quan điểm giữa các học giả về thời gian con người bắt đầu định cư (người nói 20.</span><span class=\"\">000 năm,</span><span class=\"\"> người nói 8.</span><span class=\"\">000 năm).</span><span class=\"\"> Đây chính là hành động tóm tắt một cuộc tranh luận học thuật (</span><em class=\"\">scholarly debate</em><span class=\"\">).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">29. The writer refers to the ‘late’ model in order to</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">A. compare it with another theory of migration.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “The late model demands a hypothetical migration…</span><span class=\"\"> many scholars now support the idea of an </span><strong class=\"\">early model</strong><span class=\"\"> that sees the migration as a less ordered migration,</span><span class=\"\"> and this is surely the </span><strong class=\"\">most realistic scenario</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả nhắc đến mô hình “muộn” (</span><em class=\"\">late model</em><span class=\"\">) chủ yếu để đặt nó cạnh mô hình “sớm” (</span><em class=\"\">early model</em><span class=\"\">) nhằm so sánh tính khả thi của chúng.</span><span class=\"\"> Tác giả cho rằng mô hình sớm thực tế hơn vì tính đến sự thích nghi dần dần với môi trường.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">30. What is the writer’s main point about the ‘early’ model?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">D. It is more consistent with the physical conditions of the land.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “…</span><span class=\"\">this is surely the most realistic scenario as </span><strong class=\"\">migrants slowly adapted to the diverse natural habitats</strong><span class=\"\"> they would have met while travelling through the continent.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Điểm chính của mô hình “sớm” là nó phù hợp với thực tế địa lý và sinh học,</span><span class=\"\"> cho phép con người có thời gian thích nghi với các môi trường sống đa dạng khi di chuyển qua lục địa,</span><span class=\"\"> thay vì một làn sóng di cư nhanh chóng nhưng phi lý.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">31. What does the writer suggest about the Monte Verde site?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">B. It provides supporting evidence for relatively early settlement.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 4) “Nevertheless,</span><span class=\"\"> evidence for human occupation…</span><span class=\"\"> is now </span><strong class=\"\">securely dated to around 12,500 years ago at the Monte Verde site, which casts doubt on the late model</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vì địa điểm Monte Verde có bằng chứng xác thực về con người từ 12.500 năm trước (vượt qua mốc 8.000 năm của mô hình muộn), nó đóng vai trò là bằng chứng ủng hộ cho lý thuyết định cư sớm (<em>early settlement</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('42870207-21df-4e93-b8d0-f6eb3cc3e628', '977415ad-9aad-40d7-9f51-258d1028b93d', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Information about School Registration</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Grade Level:</strong> kindergarten<br />
<strong>School:</strong> {Monterey} Heights Elementary School<br />
<strong>Registration:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Monday to Thursday from 9.00 to 1.30</li>
<li>Can pick up packet from the school {library}  any afternoon up to 5.00</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Forms:</strong> Immunisation records</p>
<ul>
<li>Heal forms from doctor and {dentist}</li>
<li>Emergency contact information</li>
<li>Residency verification form</li>
<li>Original birth certificate</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Childcare:</strong> No {transportation} is provided</p>
<ul>
<li>There is on-site licensed daycare for working {parents}</li>
<li>This is organised by the City {Youth} Council</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Orientation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Open house in July – details provided through the {mail} and on the school’s website</li>
<li>Will tour the school, meet the {teacher} and schedule entrance testing</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Schedule:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>First day of school will be on {August 19}</li>
<li>First week is 8.00 to 12.30</li>
<li>Regular schedule is 8.00 to {2:05}</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 1</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Good afternoon Lemon Grove School District.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Hi, I’m calling for information on school registration. I think my son should attend one of the schools in your district.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> What grade will your son be entering?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> He just turned 5. He’ll be starting school this year.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Oh okay. Um, one moment please. I’ll get the information for kindergarten registration.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, thank you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Uh, can you give me your address?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, it’s 7 4 1 8 Dimarino street.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Okay thanks. Yes, at that address, your child should attend <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">(1) Monterey</strong></span> Heights Elementary.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can you spell that please?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes, it’s M-O-N-T-E-R-E-Y heights.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great. So how do I register him?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> We have registration at each school site Monday through Thursday from 9 to 1. Oh no sorry, 1:30. You’ll need to pick up a kindergarten registration packet from the school beforehand though. It has all the forms you’ll need to fill out.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can I pick up the packet anytime?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Sure, the school office is usually open till 3:30 in the afternoons. Oh no, I can’t really get there that early. Well, the school has late office hours until 4 on Thursdays, or I think you can pick up a packet in the school <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">(2) library</strong></span> any day before 5.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh okay. I’ll stop by there some day this week then before 5. Can you tell me what forms we’ll need?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> I’m sure you need his immunization records.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes those.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> And we also need a general health history signed by your child’s doctor, a form filled out by the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(3) dentist</strong></span>, emergency contact information, and a residency verification form with proof of residence. Oh, and an original birth certificate.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> OK that shouldn’t be a problem. Can I ask one more question?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Sure, go ahead.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> I was wondering about before and after school care. Do you provide <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(4) transportation</strong></span> after school?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> No unfortunately, we don’t. Parents or caregivers need to pick up the children. There is however, an on-site licensed daycare for working <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">(5) parents</strong></span> who need after school care for their children. It’s housed within the school grounds and someone from the daycare will walk to the main school building to pick up your child each day. It’s run by the city <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"365\">(6) Youth</strong></span> Council and comes highly recommended.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can I get information about that as well?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes, uh, flyers and contact information will be included with your packet.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay thank you.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"29\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh and one more thing. I saw a flyer recently for an introduction event for new students and parents—an open house I think it was called, but I can’t remember the date. Was it August 3rd?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> That must have been last year’s flyer. We haven’t put out information on this year’s open house yet, but it’ll probably be sometime in August. Ah no, actually it will be in July this year, since school starts a little early this year. Once your child is registered, you’ll get all that information in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"315\">(7) mail</strong></span> and it’ll be on the school website as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great. I’m assuming that during the open house we get to tour the school and meet our child’s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">(8) teacher</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes and you will set up a time for kindergarten entrance testing as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Wow, testing already. That starts early.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well we want to make sure children are properly placed and qualified for special services if necessary.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, I guess that makes sense. Oh, and the first day of school?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> The first day will be <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">(9) August 19</strong></span>. We start in the middle of the week to help with the adjustment. And for kindergartners, the first three days are half days from 8 to 12:30.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> And then the next week the regular schedule, 8:00 to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">(10) 2:05</strong></span> will be in force.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, and you can access the full school calendar of holidays and breaks on the school website. Oh yeah, I’ve seen that. The website is very helpful. Thank you so much for your time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"41\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> You’re welcome sir.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d803e68a-f1eb-4c11-982d-63b8aef49bef', '6c33ed33-2827-4abc-97cc-53faf4fe8120', 'fillup', 'Questions 11-15', '<p>Complete the sentences below</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer</p>
<p>Special conditions may apply to {overseas} students looking for a<br />job.</p>
<p>The university Job Centre is located on the {Woodside} Campus.</p>
<p>The Job Centre remains open until {8pm} every evening.</p>
<p>The only day the employment lawyer is available is {Tuesday}</p>
<p>The university {website} regularly advertises new jobs</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SECTION 2</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Marissa:</strong> Hi, thanks for coming along. My name is Marissa and I’m going to tell you a bit about finding part-time jobs. Not everybody wants to work when they’re studying, and as this is your first year, you may feel that you’ve quite enough to do as it is. But you may change your mind or find that you need to earn some extra cash.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">However, if you are a student from <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(11) overseas</u></strong><u>,</u></span> there may be particular conditions attached to working in this country, so you should check with the staff at the centre before applying for a job.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Right now, the university has its own Job Centre on the campus. Well, actually it’s not on this main Hilston campus; it’s based in the Student Services building on the campus called <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(12) Woodside</u></strong> (spelt W-O-O-D-S-I-D-E). </span>The centre works on a drop-in basis, which means that you don’t have to make an appointment. It’s open six days a week, Monday to Saturday, and nine hours a day, from 10 in the morning until <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(13) 8 at night (8pm)</u></strong></span><u>.</u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The centre is run by other students, but a professional employment lawyer is on hand every<u> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(14) Tuesday</strong></span></u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> </span>if you want any advice about your job. There may be a queue, in which case you will have to wait, so make sure you allow plenty of time. Part-time jobs become available almost every day, and they are advertised on the university <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(15) website</u></strong>, </span>which you can access through the library if the computer centre is closed. You should check things daily, and if you see a job which interests you, call in at the centre.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Marissa:</strong> There’s a good variety of jobs on offer in the university itself just now. For example, they’re looking for people to check that all the vehicles using the university <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(16) car parks</u></strong><u> have got up-to-date permits <strong>(C)</strong></u>. </span>Office jobs rarely come up, but in future, the university is hoping to be able to offer jobs in the IT centre.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are also recruitment open days which are held <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(17) regularly during the year (C: throughout the year)</u></strong><u>,</u></span> when local employers come into the university to recruit students for part-time work within their company. These two-day events are scheduled well in advance each term and are advertised in the usual places.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Of course, part-time work is useful to supplement your income, but it’s also a valuable way of<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> </span><strong><u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">(18) building up an employment record that reflects your skills and capabilities (B: provide a useful work record for the</span> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">future)</span></u></strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><u>. </u></span>One of the most common complaints of graduates leaving university is that many jobs require proven experience, so those applicants who have evidence of part-time work on their CV often have an advantage.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Job Centre advertises jobs which will give you skills such as using word processing packages, spreadsheets or supervisory skills. So if you have to work, use the opportunity to develop skills which will help you secure a job in the future.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, what about the financial side of things? Well, students who work part-time can no longer expect to be paid cash.<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong><u>(19) An employer will deduct tax from what you earn (A: will be taxed)</u></strong></span><u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">,</span> </u>but depending on your own individual circumstances and how much you earn in a year, you should be able to reclaim some of this. You may also have to contribute towards an insurance scheme, but you must ask your employer about these deductions.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You should also check whether you will be paid weekly or monthly and if you work extra hours, what your overtime rate will be. It’s also necessary to make sure that your employer knows that you may only be able to work during term time. Communication between you and your employer is very important, but don’t expect all employers to use email. If you are ill or cannot get into work for whatever reason, make sure your employer knows in good time—that shouldn’t be a problem now that everyone has a mobile phone. And if you decide to leave the job, you should make sure you<u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong>(20) put this in writing (A: give notice in writing)</strong>.</span> </u>Some employers require a month’s notice, even for a part-time job.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">So what sort of work can you expect to find? Well, as I said earlier…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7a644555-39f8-4c27-bc66-b3ebd2231f7c', '6c33ed33-2827-4abc-97cc-53faf4fe8120', 'radio', 'Questions 16-20', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "its offices"}, {"content": "the IT centre"}, {"content": "the car parks"}], "question": "At present, the university is offering part-time work in"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "only in the first term"}, {"content": "twice a term"}, {"content": "throughout the year"}], "question": "Local employers visit the university"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "lead to a full-time job after graduation"}, {"content": "provide a useful work record for the future"}, {"content": "give the chance to develop team-work skills"}], "question": "According to the speaker, a part-time job can"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "will be taxed"}, {"content": "will be paid every week"}, {"content": "will need private insurance"}], "question": "Students who work part-time"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "give notice in writing"}, {"content": "communicate by email"}, {"content": "have a mobile phone"}], "question": "Part-time student workers are advised to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('06768a8c-b671-4ba1-a8c9-34dfa17eef5b', '3d515b65-71d6-4925-9fac-a72d6f3d6c5e', 'matching', 'Questions 11–16', '', '<p>What tourist attraction does each of the following locations have?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the corrct letter, <strong>A</strong>- <strong>I</strong>, next to Questions 11-16</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1,0,0\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Locations</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,0,0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,0,0\">Sheepfold: {I hills}</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,1,0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,1,0\">Brown Mare {H wild flowers}</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,2,0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,2,0\">Doris {B nature reserve}</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,3,0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,3,0\">Lodge Estate {E newly born deer}</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,4,0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,4,0\">Aurden {D old ruins}</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,5,0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1,5,0\">Eastlake: {F birds}</p>", "optionsTitle": "List of Options", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A farming life in the past"}, {"optionText": "B Nature reserve"}, {"optionText": "C canoes"}, {"optionText": "D old ruins"}, {"optionText": "E newly born deer"}, {"optionText": "F birds"}, {"optionText": "G waterfalls"}, {"optionText": "H wild flowers"}, {"optionText": "I hills "}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sally:</strong> Good morning, everyone. I’m Sally, tour guide from Travel-lite Travel Agency. Today, I’m going to introduce a great trip to Southern Scotland for you. I’m sure you will find it a fantastic place. There is lots to see in Southern Scotland.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">To begin with, we will go to Sheepfold, which has one or two beautiful gardens. One thing that’s definitely worth doing is climbing to the top of the mountain. You’ll be fascinated by the beautiful scenery alongside the mountain road. When you get to the top, you can overlook the coastline and enjoy the stunning view. <strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"320\">{I hills}</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">From there, we will go on to Brown Mare. Brown Mare used to be famous for its farm, but it is being refurbished at the moment and isn’t likely to be reopened by the time we go there. But you can walk for hours there in the peaceful green surroundings along a wide variety of tracks. I think you’ll be struck by the beautiful roses and mother nature. <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"350\">{H wild flowers}</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">In Doris, there were several old barns, but they have been converted into a special section where animals and plants are protected. From there, you can see a range of rare breeds, as well as flowers. This place is usually favored by university students as a destination for their field trips. <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"293\">{B nature reserve}</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Then, we will go to Lodge Estate, which is the most favorite location for children, as they can watch the baby deer. But remember, don’t give food to them. Photography is allowed there, and when you leave, you can get one free photo at the exit. But please don’t move rocks or branches to take photos. You should leave the site intact. <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"336\">{E newly born deer}</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Our next stop is Orton (Aurden). I strongly recommend that you visit the ancient town which was constructed nearly 1,000 years ago. There is not much of the original buildings left, but still plenty to see. The site is being excavated, and you’ll be able to help out if you want to. <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"283\">{D old ruins}</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Finally, we will spend some time in East Lake, which changes with the seasons, with different events happening at different times of the year. At the moment when we arrive there, it will be the most spectacular month with the arrival of Canada geese. I’m pretty sure that this visit will give you an unforgettable experience. <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"326\">{F birds}</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ACCOMMODATION &amp; BENEFITS (Questions 17–20)</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sally:</strong> Some of you have asked me about the place where we’re going to stay. So next, I will introduce different types of accommodation there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">First, many tourists may consider visiting a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">bed and breakfast</strong>, also called a B&amp;B, as they don’t have to be worried about what to eat in the morning. But you have to pay attention that this type of accommodation is only available on a daily basis.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The cheapest possible option is to stay in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">hostel</strong>, but you should be aware that sometimes you are provided with only a single bed with several people sharing the same room, and meals are not included. But some people think they have never had such an experience before that they want to have a try. More importantly, they don’t have to change accommodation for a whole week.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">For those who want to visit the castles, I recommend you stay in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">cottages</strong> nearby with beautiful surroundings. The owner promises that the rent can be paid every seven days, so just be relieved to have a peaceful life there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">For our members, I will introduce some benefits you can get from our travel agency. As for the accommodation I just mentioned, someone has asked if we offer a <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">discount</strong>. I’m afraid to tell you this is only for premium members, who can benefit from 10% off the original price.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">For those self-driving travelers, you might be interested in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">parking space</strong>. This is always limited at the hotel, so we only offer free parking service to premium members as well, I’m afraid. Ordinary members have to pay a fee for parking.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\">The good news is, all of you can enjoy your <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">guide service</strong> without any charge, including the visit to attractions like the castles. But remember, the entrance fee has to be paid by yourself.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\">Oh, I nearly forgot! You can also receive regular copies of <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">magazines</strong> about the native food and attractions in Scotland, absolutely for free. It’s a gift for you. I hope you will like it. Okay, that’s all I want to share today. If you have any more questions about the trip, please call me.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bf8bbb3f-42d3-4233-9198-bbb51afbf390', '735307d3-4167-47f0-a0d3-b096f8c7581a', 'radio', 'Questions 21-26', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Research Project.</strong></span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "He thought the information would be useful for town planning"}, {"content": "He has a special interest in the use of public services"}, {"content": "He read about a similar study which had been done earlier"}], "question": "How did John choose the topic of his research project?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "The use of public services has altered very littl"}, {"content": "A group of people has changed its habits"}, {"content": "The most frequently used facility is the library"}], "question": "During his research, John is expecting to find tha"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "They may be lacking in details"}, {"content": "They may not be readily available"}, {"content": "They may be difficult to analyse"}], "question": "What is the problem with using official records?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "He needs to do a course in questionnaire design first"}, {"content": "He should use his method instead of looking at public records"}, {"content": " He will find the practice he gets useful the following year"}], "question": "What does the tutor think about John using a questionnaire to get information?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Occupation"}, {"content": "Income group"}, {"content": "Qualifications"}], "question": "Which new variable does John agree to add to his investigation?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "The same number as in the previous study"}, {"content": "A greater number than he needs for analysis"}, {"content": "The number recommended in the project guidelines"}], "question": "How many questionnaires will John distribute?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SECTION 3</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Hello John, come in and sit down. You’re here to discuss your research project, are you?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Yes, I’ve more or less decided what to do, but I’d like your opinion.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Fine. You’ve chosen a topic?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Yes, I want to look at how people use public services in their local area—things like parks and swimming pools.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Right, well, the kind of information you’ll get is very useful for town planning, of course. Do you have a special interest in public services?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Not really. It’s just that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21) I found a report in the college library about an investigation that was done 10 years ago and I thought it would be interesting to do a parallel one (C: read about a similar study)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Hmm, 10 years is a relatively short space of time. What do you expect to find? Do you think things will be more or less the same as before?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> I think there will be some differences. For example, I think the number of people going to the library will have decreased… and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(22) I’d guess that older people are using the sports centre more often than they used to (B: A group of people has changed its habits)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Fine, so those are your hypotheses. Now what sort of data are you going to use?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> I was thinking of using official records from the management or the local council and analysing them. They should be easy to obtain. I don’t think that sort of information would be confidential.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Yes, you’re probably right. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23) There might not be as much information as you’d like (A: lacking in details)</strong></span>, but it would certainly be the easiest kind of data to work with. But have you considered using a questionnaire as well? It’s OK to get data from more than one source.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong>It’s OK to get data from more than one source</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong>Absolutely. It’s a bonus<strong>.</strong> You’ve already done the module on questionnaire design, haven’t you? And <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(24) it’ll be good to get experience because next year you’ll have to do something similar for your final dissertation on a bigger scale (C: find the practice he gets useful the following year)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> OK.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> And what are the variables you’ll be looking at? Are you going to look at people’s level of education—whether they have a degree, for example?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> I hadn’t planned to. Do you think I should?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Well, you might see some interesting patterns.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(25) Okay, and that’ll tie in nicely with my plans (C: Qualifications)</strong></span> to analyze the kind of work people do.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor: </strong>Hmm, what about the size of your sample? Have you got any thoughts on the number of questionnaires you might send out? </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> The previous study surveyed 120 people.I don’t think I can really analyze more than 50 working by myself. So<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(26) I should probably distribute about 80 questionnaires altogether to allow for wastage (B: A greater number than he needs for analysis)</strong></span>. Do you think that’s enough?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Definitely. I know that your project guidelines recommend a minimum of 100, but that’s an ideal number and you’re working by yourself.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> And think of ways you can encourage people to actually complete the questionnaire. For example, to make sure that your questions make sense, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(27/28) you should try them out beforehand (E: Trialing the questionnaire on friends)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Okay, that’s no problem, my friends will help.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Good. Sometimes you get unpredictable responses and you have to rephrase a question</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:. </strong>And I know that you usually get a better return if you deliver questionnaires in person, but there will be too many. But <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(27/28) I could enclose a stamped envelope for the return post (D: Providing return envelopes)</strong>.</span> It’s a bit expensive, but I think it would be worth it.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Yes, good. Some people say that another way of increasing returns is to make the questionnaires anonymous, but usually people put their names on anyway, so I don’t think that would make much difference.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> <strong>John:</strong>Okay, and can you give me a bit more advice about the questionnaire? Would it be a good idea to have <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29/30) a short paragraph at the top explaining what I’m doing and why (C: introduction to explain survey’s purpose)</strong></span>?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Definitely. And don’t forget you’ll need to<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(29/30) get a bit of information about your subjects—what age group they’re in (B: elicit personal information)</strong>,</span> and perhaps how long they’ve lived in the area. So you’ll need questions for that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Ah yes, I suppose that will mean it takes a bit longer to complete. But should I give them my phone number in case there’s anything they’re not sure about?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> I wouldn’t if I were you, no.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> OK, and do I have to use open-ended questions as well as closed questions?I know the books say it’s better to have a mixture.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> Well, it depends. In this case, I’d stick to closed questions. The results will be much more manageable like that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">John:</strong> If I draft some questions tomorrow, would it be OK to bring them to&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0ec77dd3-3d25-46cd-8696-013c37ecfe70', '20f74f65-857f-4588-b75d-4fb6ba00146f', 'matching', 'Questions 11–15', '', '<p data-start="122" data-end="217">Complete the flow-chart below.<br data-start="152" data-end="155">Choose <strong>FIVE </strong>correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>I</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"219\" data-end=\"244\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">How to use City Cycle</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"246\" data-end=\"297\">Subscribe to the service online to receive a card</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"304\" data-end=\"353\">At the station, log on at the computer terminal</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"360\" data-end=\"400\">Select a bike by using the {screen}</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"407\" data-end=\"470\">Release the bike by using the {button} of your chosen bike</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"477\" data-end=\"541\">Remove the bike from the {rack}<br data-start=\"513\" data-end=\"516\">(You have ten seconds.)</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"548\" data-end=\"601\">Make sure you have a {helmet} before setting off</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"745\">At the end of your journey, return the bike to a station and secure in place</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"745\">(A {light} will tell you the bike is locked correctly)</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "button"}, {"optionText": "website"}, {"optionText": "helmet"}, {"optionText": "light"}, {"optionText": "locker"}, {"optionText": "password"}, {"optionText": "rack"}, {"optionText": "screen"}, {"optionText": "sound"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 2: BICYCLE INITIATIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Thank you for all coming to today’s information session on bicycle use in the inner city.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">I’ll start by telling you about the City Council’s new bicycle hire scheme, which is called City Cycle. We want to provide people who don’t own a bike a convenient way to get around the inner city.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Now to use City Cycle, first you need to subscribe to the service, and you can do that online. Just go to the city council website and follow the prompts and you’ll be sent a card.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Once you’ve done that you can unlock one of our bikes from any station in the inner city area. Just go to the station and log on at the computer terminal.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">You’ll be shown a diagram of the bikes that are currently available at the station, so you just choose the one you want by touching the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">(11) screen [H]</strong></span>. You don’t need a password or anything.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Once you’ve chosen your bike, you can then go to where the bikes are stored and push the release <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"97\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(12) button</span> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">[A]</span></strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">After you do that, you have about 10 seconds to take the bike out of the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">(13) rack [G]</strong></span>. You can now start your bike ride.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Further down the track, we’re thinking about adding lockers for bags if the scheme is popular. Oh, at this point can I just clarify something that a few people have been asking, and that is do I have to wear a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"210\">(14) helmet [C]</strong></span>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Well the answer is yes, you do. That’s a requirement by law in this state, so don’t forget to wear one at all times when riding.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Now at the end of your trip, just come back to one of the city cycle stations and wheel the bike into the bike rack. It’s important to make sure that the bike is properly secured because you could be held liable if it goes missing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">The green<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"10\">(15) light [D]</strong></span> on the rack will confirm that it has been locked into place. So we hope that with such a simple scheme will have many users.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">BICYCLE CENTRE PLAN</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Let’s turn to another initiative: the layout of the new council bicycle centre, which will be opening next week.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">This is for people who already own a bike. We wanted to provide a place for cyclists to store their bikes, then change before going on to work. Can you all see the plan?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\">If you look at the bottom towards the right-hand corner, you’ll see where the cyclists enter the centre. People want more than just a place to park their bikes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\">That’s why you’ll see a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(16) coffee cart [E]</strong></span>. That’s it there, between the reception desk and the vending machines. I’m sure it’ll be very popular with commuters first thing in the morning.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">Now of course, some of our cyclists have very expensive bikes, so we’ll have a totally secure place for them to park. That’s it in the top right-hand corner.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">Now there’s another special service for the cyclists that I’d like to show you. Look back at the entry on the map. Just to the left of reception, on the Donovan Street side of the building, you’ll see quite a large room.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">That’s the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">(17) workshop [F]</strong></span> where cyclists will be able to leave their bikes for repairs while they are at work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\">We’ve put a lot of thought into the facilities of the centre. If you have any valuables with you, you can leave these in our <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">(18) lockers [A]</strong></span>. The locker room is in the top left-hand corner of your plan, so you can store your bag or wallet there before you head off for a shower.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\">We’ve installed 10 state-of-the-art power <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">(19) showers [H]</strong></span>. They are located in this room here, to the left of the hair dryers and just near the exit.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\">There’s also a water cooler available so you can grab a drink, and then pick up a<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">(20) towel [B]</strong> </span>next to the water cooler there.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('48804a3f-ee03-4379-b4ff-169e26555fe1', '20f74f65-857f-4588-b75d-4fb6ba00146f', 'matrix', 'Questions 16–20', '', '<p data-start="895" data-end="975">Label the plan below.<br data-start="916" data-end="919">Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>H</strong></p>
<h3 data-start="977" data-end="1002"><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="506" height="456" loading="lazy"></h3>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Coffee cart", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Workshop", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Lockers", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Showers", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "Towel", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('af2f690c-5b0e-4b35-a109-e596e71375e6', '677f54f1-5801-4951-ae40-b2a57b129495', 'matching', 'Questions 14–20', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Global resistance to lean manufacturing"}, {"optionText": "ii The historical context"}, {"optionText": "iii Procedures for controlling quality"}, {"optionText": "iv The pros and cons of different production systems"}, {"optionText": "v The impact on profits"}, {"optionText": "vi Procedures for controlling supply"}, {"optionText": "vii The origin of the term"}, {"optionText": "viii A crucial difference in levels of quality"}, {"optionText": "ix Working conditions"}, {"optionText": "x Interdependent strategies for controlling expenditure"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>14. Paragraph A</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: ii. The historical context</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A đặt Lean Production vào bối cảnh lịch sử, so sánh nó với Mass Production (Henry Ford) và Craft Production, và nêu nguồn gốc của nó (Eiji Toyoda và Taiichi Ohno) ở Nhật Bản.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>15. Paragraph B</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: iv. The pros and cons of different production systems</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B so sánh ba hệ thống sản xuất chính (Craft, Mass, Lean), tập trung vào ưu điểm (pros) và nhược điểm (cons) của từng loại (ví dụ: Craft quá đắt, Mass quá cứng nhắc và gây chán nản cho nhân viên).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>16. Paragraph C</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: vii. The origin of the term</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C giải thích thuật ngữ “Lean Production” được đặt tên như vậy là do nó sử dụng <strong>ít hơn mọi thứ</strong> (“less of everything” / “half the human effort… half the manufacturing space…”).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>17. Paragraph D</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: viii. A crucial difference in levels of quality</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D tập trung vào sự khác biệt nổi bật giữa hai hệ thống: Mass Production đặt mục tiêu “good enough” (chấp nhận một số lỗi), còn Lean Production <strong>không chấp nhận thỏa hiệp</strong> (“unwilling to compromise standards”) về chất lượng (far fewer defects).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>18. Paragraph E</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: x. Interdependent strategies for controlling expenditure</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E nêu mục tiêu chính là <strong>giảm chi phí</strong> (cost reduction / expenditure), nhưng phải đạt được ba mục tiêu trung gian khác: kiểm soát số lượng (quantity control), đảm bảo chất lượng (quality assurance) và tôn trọng con người (respect for humanity). Ba mục tiêu này <strong>phụ thuộc lẫn nhau</strong> (“none of these three objectives can be achieved separately”).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>19. Paragraph F</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: vi. Procedures for controlling supply</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F mô tả cơ chế <strong>just-in-time</strong> (JIT). JIT là một thủ tục kiểm soát việc <strong>cung cấp</strong> (supply) linh kiện và vật liệu sao cho chúng đến đúng thời điểm và số lượng cần thiết.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>20. Paragraph G</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: iii. Procedures for controlling quality</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G mô tả <strong>autonamation</strong> (tự động hóa), cơ chế kiểm tra sự bất thường (abnormalities) trong quá trình sản xuất. Mục đích là đảm bảo <strong>chất lượng</strong> (quality control) song song với JIT, ngăn ngừa sự nhân lên của các lỗi.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('949e312e-c10e-4b58-b15c-259daa8b795e', 'b4e3507e-d022-4952-bbbd-edb2e33529c6', 'radio', 'Questions 32-35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The conditions encountered by the first migrants to Patagonia were unique."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the high country the first migrants hunted wild animals for food."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Archaeologists have failed to draw conclusions from the evidence found at rock shelters in Argentina and Chile."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Archaeological evidence can be moved from place to place in a variety of ways."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">32. The conditions encountered by the first migrants to Patagonia were unique.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…allowed the initial human intrusion into a pristine environment, which was <strong>similar to that of early post-glacial Europe</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc cho biết môi trường nguyên sơ mà những người di cư đầu tiên gặp phải tại Patagonia <strong>tương tự</strong> (<em>similar</em>) như ở Châu Âu thời kỳ đầu hậu kỷ băng hà. Văn bản không khẳng định những điều kiện này là “duy nhất” (<em>unique</em>) hay chưa từng có ở nơi nào khác trên thế giới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">33. In the high country the first migrants hunted wild animals for food.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “Human settlement of the vast horizontal expanse of treeless high country must have been tenuous at best, and the evidence for this occupation remains relatively scant…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù bài đọc có nhắc đến việc tìm thấy xương động vật ở một số địa điểm khác (như Las Buitreras), nhưng tại khu vực <strong>vùng cao</strong> (<em>high country</em>), bằng chứng về sự cư trú rất ít ỏi (<em>scant</em>). Tác giả không đề cập cụ thể liệu những người di cư ở vùng này có săn bắt động vật hoang dã để làm thức ăn hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">34. Archaeologist have failed to draw conclusions from the evidence found at rock shelters in Argentina and Chile.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…most of it coming from rock shelters in Argentina and Chile. There is, however, <strong>reliable evidence from these sites to confirm the presence of humans</strong> by around 11,000 years ago in different habitats…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói các nhà khảo cổ đã “thất bại” (<em>failed</em>) trong việc đưa ra kết luận. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc khẳng định đã có <strong>bằng chứng đáng tin cậy</strong> từ các mái đá này để <strong>xác nhận</strong> sự hiện diện của con người cách đây khoảng 11.000 năm. Vì thông tin trong bài bác bỏ ý kiến “thất bại”, đáp án là <strong>NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">35. Archaeological evidence can be moved from place to place in a variety of ways.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…anthropologists have come to recognise that bones or other evidence may be <strong>deposited in caves by natural agency, in other words by other forces such as floods or predators</strong>, and not necessarily by humans.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc xác nhận rằng các bằng chứng khảo cổ (như xương) có thể được đưa vào hang động bởi các <strong>tác nhân tự nhiên</strong> (<em>natural agency</em>) như <strong>lũ lụt hoặc động vật săn mồi</strong> (<em>floods or predators</em>). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc bằng chứng có thể bị di chuyển từ nơi này sang nơi khác bằng nhiều cách khác nhau, đúng với khẳng định của câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9168010a-6cdd-4f4f-99fe-586dc82e2c47', '735307d3-4167-47f0-a0d3-b096f8c7581a', 'checkbox', 'Questions 27-28', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>&#8211;<strong>E</strong></p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>strategies will John use to encourage people to fill out his questionnaire?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. Using simple language", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. Delivering the questionnaires in person", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. Making the questionnaires anonymous", "correct": false}, {"option": "D. Providing return envelopes", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. Trialing the questionnaire on friends", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('03de85f3-45cd-47fb-9a19-3fdd00567a4d', 'b6ad2630-66cd-4a7b-beab-cad8431ae4f7', 'radio', 'Questions 1-8', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the early 19th century, the port of London was considered a safer destination than other ports"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "London Bridge provided quick access for cargo being sent to southern Britain"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It was generally believed that a new river crossing would be profitable"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Building a second bridge crossing was initially considered to be the best solution"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It was believed that coal could be found under the River Thames"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Thames Archway Company was the first group to try tunnelling below the Thames"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some of Trevithick''s men were injured during a mudslide at his tunnel"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Thames Archway Company ran out of money to finance the tunnel project"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. In the early 19th century, the port of London was considered a safer destination than other ports.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;At the beginning of the 19th century, the port of London was the busiest in the world. Cargoes that had travelled thousands of miles and survived all the hazards of the sea were unloaded&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu rằng cảng London rất bận rộn và hàng hóa đã vượt qua các nguy hiểm trên biển để đến đây. Tuy nhiên, không có thông tin nào so sánh độ an toàn của cảng London với các cảng khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. London Bridge provided quick access for cargo being sent to southern Britain.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;London Bridge, built in the 12th century and as impractical as its early date implies. By 1820, London Bridge had become the centre of the world’s largest traffic jam.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cây cầu này rất bất tiện và là trung tâm của sự tắc nghẽn giao thông lớn nhất thế giới, vì vậy nó không thể cung cấp sự tiếp cận nhanh chóng cho hàng hóa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. It was generally believed that a new river crossing would be profitable.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;it was clear that if private enterprise could build another crossing closer to the docks, there would be good money to be made in tolls paid by users.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản khẳng định rằng nếu xây dựng được một lối băng qua sông mới, chủ đầu tư sẽ thu được rất nhiều tiền từ phí cầu đường của người dân.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Building a second bridge crossing was initially considered to be the best solution.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Another bridge was out of the question, as this would deny sailing ships access to the city centre&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc xây một cây cầu khác là &#8220;không thể bàn tới&#8221; vì nó sẽ ngăn cản tàu buồm đi vào trung tâm thành phố. Do đó, nó chưa bao giờ được coi là giải pháp tốt nhất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. It was believed that coal could be found under the River Thames.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Although increasing demand for coal had meant a great many tunnels had been dug in mines in Britain, working methods remained primitive.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Than đá được nhắc đến như lý do khiến kỹ thuật đào hầm mỏ phát triển ở Anh, nhưng không có thông tin nào nói rằng người ta tin có than dưới lòng sông Thames.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. The Thames Archway Company was the first group to try tunnelling below the Thames.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Their ambition was to tunnel below the Thames, but there was little to guide them as there had been no previous attempt to do this.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trước dự án của công ty này vào năm 1807, chưa từng có nỗ lực nào khác để đào hầm dưới sông Thames được thực hiện.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Some of Trevithick&#8217;s men were injured during a mudslide at his tunnel.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;things began to go disastrously wrong, with muddy soil pouring into the tunnel.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nói về sự cố bùn tràn vào hầm, nhưng không đề cập đến việc có công nhân nào bị thương hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. The Thames Archway Company ran out of money to finance the tunnel project.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Eventually, the Thames Archway Company had had enough. Its funds were exhausted&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ &#8220;funds were exhausted&#8221; có nghĩa là nguồn vốn đã cạn kiệt hoàn toàn, đồng nghĩa với việc hết tiền để tài trợ dự án.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bef83561-7d78-4844-a909-f133c06b203b', '1309e07e-3d9f-487e-a665-b3c72c540cc1', 'fillup', 'Questions 17–22', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>What makes us procrastinate?</strong></p>
<p>Many people think that procrastination is the result of {laziness}.<br />Others believe it to be the result of an inability to organise time efficiently.</p>
<p>But scientific studies suggest that procrastination is actually due to poor mood management. The tasks we are most likely to put off are those that could damage our self-esteem or cause us to feel {anxious} when we think about them. Research comparing chronic procrastinators with other people even found differences in the brain regions associated with regulating emotions and identifying {threats}.</p>
<p>Emotionally loaded and difficult tasks often cause us to procrastinate. Getting ready to take {exams} might be a typical example of one such task.</p>
<p>People who are likely to procrastinate tend to be either {perfectionists} or those with low self-esteem.</p>
<p>Procrastination is only a short-term measure for managing emotions. It’s often followed by a feeling of {guilt}, which worsens our mood and leads to more procrastination.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>17. laziness<br />(Đoạn B: “Contrary to popular belief, procrastination is not due to laziness or poor time management.”)<br />→ Nhiều người nghĩ trì hoãn là do lười biếng, nhưng thực ra không phải vậy.</p>\n<p> <br />18. anxious<br />(Đoạn B: “If just thinking about the task threatens our sense of self-worth or makes us anxious, we will be more likely to put it off.”)<br />→ Khi nghĩ đến công việc khiến ta lo lắng (anxious) hoặc sợ hại đến lòng tự trọng, ta càng dễ trì hoãn.</p>\n<p> <br />19. threats<br />(Đoạn B: “Areas of the brain linked to detection of threats and emotion regulation are actually different in people who chronically procrastinate…” )<br />→ Nghiên cứu cho thấy sự khác biệt ở vùng não liên quan đến việc phát hiện mối đe dọa (threats) và điều tiết cảm xúc.</p>\n<p> <br />20. exams<br />(Đoạn C: “Tasks that are emotionally loaded or difficult, such as preparing for exams, are prime candidates for procrastination.”)<br />→ Một ví dụ điển hình của công việc dễ bị trì hoãn là chuẩn bị cho kỳ thi (exams).</p>\n<p> <br />21. perfectionists<br />(Đoạn C: “Another group of people who tend to procrastinate are perfectionists, who worry their work will be judged harshly by others.”)<br />→ Những người cầu toàn (perfectionists) thường trì hoãn vì sợ công việc bị đánh giá không hoàn hảo.</p>\n<p> <br />22. guilt<br />(Đoạn C: “Afterwards, people tend to be left with a sense of guilt that not only increases their negative mood, but also reinforces their tendency to procrastinate.”)<br />→ Sau khi trì hoãn, con người thường cảm thấy tội lỗi (guilt), điều này làm xấu tâm trạng và khiến họ tiếp tục trì hoãn.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('854f66d5-e8f8-46e0-85fd-ddf79a9cfd5f', 'b4e3507e-d022-4952-bbbd-edb2e33529c6', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words and phrases, A-J, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The archaeological evidence from Patagonia</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Building remains and other evidence have been found in {D good condition} at the Chinchihuapi Creek site, and because of this it has been possible to date them to around 12,500 years ago. However, the {B random collection} of the samples taken from Los Toldos means that this site is of doubtful value. El Ceibo is a more promising dig, where the examination of artefacts would be beneficial in order to confirm the usefulness of discoveries there. The remains found at the Arroyo Feo site show {C similar properties} and date from around 9,000 years ago. Unfortunately no {H reliable connection} can be made between the samples taken from Las Buitreras and human presence. The findings of the work carried out at Cueva Fell cannot provide useful information beyond the {J immediate surroundings} In conclusion, though the evidence is mixed, it is believed that human population of Patagonia began about 11,000 years ago.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A fixed date"}, {"optionText": "B random collection"}, {"optionText": "C similar properties"}, {"optionText": "D good condition"}, {"optionText": "E scientific evaluation"}, {"optionText": "F huge quantities"}, {"optionText": "G new samples"}, {"optionText": "H reliable connection"}, {"optionText": "I skilled preservation"}, {"optionText": "J immediate surroundings"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">36. Building remains and other evidence have been found in <strong>D. good condition</strong> at the Chinchihuapi Creek site…</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D. good condition</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 6 (Dòng 1-4)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “At the site located beside Chinchihuapi Creek, excavations have produced convincing evidence… They were buried in layers of peat, which has the property of <strong>preserving wood remarkably well</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập rằng các hiện vật bằng gỗ tại địa điểm này được bảo quản rất tốt nhờ lớp than bùn (<em>preserving wood remarkably well</em>). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc chúng ở trong <strong>tình trạng tốt</strong> (<em>good condition</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">37. However, the <strong>B. random collection</strong> of the samples taken from Los Toldos means that this site is of doubtful value.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. random collection</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 6 (Dòng 6-8)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the evidence from this site [Los Toldos] has recently been called into question, because dispersed flecks of carbon… were taken <strong>unsystematically from many different places</strong> in the site.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc lấy mẫu một cách <strong>không hệ thống</strong> (<em>unsystematically</em>) từ nhiều nơi khác nhau tương ứng với ý nghĩa của một <strong>bộ sưu tập ngẫu nhiên</strong> (<em>random collection</em>), làm cho giá trị của địa điểm này bị nghi ngờ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">38. The remains found at the Arroyo Feo site show <strong>C. similar properties</strong> and date from around 9,000 years ago.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. similar properties</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 7 (Dòng 1-2)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The artefacts from the earliest occupations [at Arroyo Feo]… have the <strong>same origins as those from Los Toldos</strong>, and have been securely dated to around 9,000 years ago.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các hiện vật tại Arroyo Feo có cùng nguồn gốc (<em>same origins</em>) với các hiện vật tại Los Toldos, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc chúng có những <strong>đặc tính tương tự</strong> (<em>similar properties</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">39. Unfortunately no <strong>H. reliable connection</strong> can be made between the samples taken from Las Buitreras and human presence.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>H. reliable connection</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 7 (Dòng 4-6)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…at Las Buitreras… anthropologists now believe that presumed cut marks on the bones are somewhat dubious… there is <strong>no way of securely relating</strong> any of these remains with human occupation.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản khẳng định không có cách nào để <strong>liên hệ một cách chắc chắn</strong> (<em>no way of securely relating</em>) các di cốt động vật với sự hiện diện của con người. Cụm từ “reliable connection” (mối liên hệ đáng tin cậy) là cách diễn đạt tương đương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">40. The findings of the work carried out at Cueva Fell cannot provide useful information beyond the <strong>J. immediate surroundings</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>J. immediate surroundings</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 7 (Dòng 7-9)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the utility of this site [Cueva Fell] must be <strong>restricted to its direct vicinity</strong>, given changes to the nearby area… and findings cannot be freely extrapolated further afield.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tính hữu dụng của địa điểm Cueva Fell bị giới hạn trong <strong>vùng lân cận trực tiếp</strong> (<em>direct vicinity</em>). Trong danh sách từ cho sẵn, “immediate surroundings” có nghĩa tương đồng hoàn toàn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ebf7d3ae-ba3d-4a8a-bd99-dc0275518636', '735307d3-4167-47f0-a0d3-b096f8c7581a', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29-30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, A-E</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>pieces of advice does the tutor give John about his questionnaire?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. There should be a mixture of question types", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. Some questions should elicit personal information", "correct": true}, {"option": "C. There should be an introduction to explain the survey’s purpose", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. A telephone number should be provided for queries", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. The questions should only take a few minutes to answer", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('727fe006-bb66-493a-b8b4-1310b8336492', 'df332c92-4c48-41fb-ace5-f8a71801e0cc', 'fillup', 'Questions 34-37', '<p>Label the diagram below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="615" height="267" loading="lazy"></p>
<p>-network of {tunnels} helps to give the termites a constant<br>-{AIR} supply and to maintain a limited temperature range<br>-cellar to aid control of {moisture} levels in mound<br>-top of the mound permits {evaporation}</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5e68991e-bd8c-4c89-a385-e0e96b859e98', 'b6ad2630-66cd-4a7b-beab-cad8431ae4f7', 'fillup', 'Questions 9-13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text   ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Marc Brunel’s tunnel</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Preparing to build the tunnel</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Brunel noticed how a kind of {worm} made its tunnels in wood.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Brunel created a device called a tunnelling shield, to protect people working under the river.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Brunel planned to build a shallow tunnel so the earth would have a higher content of {clay} .</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Problems faced by miners</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>There were frequent floods caused by mechanical breakdowns.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The miners suffered from<strong> </strong>{headaches} because of pollution in the tunnels.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Lighting problems led to several {accidents}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Some workers quit because of the high temperatures in the tunnel.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>After the tunnel was finished</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The tunnel was finally completed in 1841.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Brunel did not have enough money to repay his debt to the {government}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The tunnel was abandoned until the 1880s.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text   ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-heading"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. worm</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">worm</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…he observed it was infested with something that looked like a worm… Brunel realised that the worm’s digging technique could be adapted to produce a new way of tunnelling.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Marc Brunel đã lấy cảm hứng từ cách một loài sâu đục gỗ tạo ra đường hầm trong gỗ để phát minh ra thiết bị đào hầm chuyên dụng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. clay</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">clay</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…decided to dig the tunnel close to the muddy river bottom, where he could expect to find clay. This would be a more solid and safe substance to dig through…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Brunel chọn đào ở tầng đất sét vì đây là vật liệu vững chắc và an toàn hơn so với lớp cát ở sâu bên dưới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. headaches</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">headaches</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “They also complained of frequent headaches and dizziness, caused by the poor air quality.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Do thiếu hệ thống thông gió, không khí ô nhiễm trong hầm đã khiến công nhân gặp các vấn đề sức khỏe như đau đầu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. accidents</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">accidents</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Lamps give off only a very weak glow, and there were a number of accidents because the miners could not see what they were doing.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ánh sáng yếu từ nến và đèn dầu khiến thợ mỏ không nhìn rõ, dẫn đến nhiều tai nạn xảy ra trong quá trình làm việc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. government</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">government</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…and the government loan he had required to complete the project had to be paid back with interest.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Brunel đã phải vay tiền từ chính phủ để hoàn thành dự án, và khoản nợ kèm lãi suất này là gánh nặng tài chính lớn sau khi hầm hoàn tất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"> </p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('df1b6a8c-def2-438c-a770-19f35d66e36d', 'b912e56f-7fb0-4900-ae9e-21d3d63fef37', 'matching', 'Questions 14–20', '', '<p>The text has seven sections. Choose the correct heading for each section and move it into the gap.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "Packaging that allows consumers to use more of the product"}, {"optionText": "The many reasons for changes in packaging"}, {"optionText": "Packaging that includes utensils like spoons and forks"}, {"optionText": "Packaging that can be consumed with its contents"}, {"optionText": "Packaging that doesn’t take up a lot of space"}, {"optionText": "The history of food packaging"}, {"optionText": "Packaging that indicates when food is beginning to go rotten"}, {"optionText": "Packaging that can be reused"}, {"optionText": "Using packaging to communicate ideas and attract customers"}, {"optionText": "Packaging that vanishes or decomposes quickly"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Section 1: Using packaging to communicate ideas and attract customers</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 1.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> &#8220;Food companies spend a lot of time thinking about packaging as a way to </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">represent their brand</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> a food container can </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">suggest playfulness, environmental consciousness, or high technology</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này nói về việc sử dụng bao bì để truyền tải thông điệp về thương hiệu (ý tưởng) và tạo ấn tượng ban đầu để thu hút khách hàng.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Section 2: The many reasons for changes in packaging</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 2.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> &#8220;Consumers are becoming increasingly </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">obsessed with sleek technology, reducing food waste, and minimizing health risks</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> In response,</span><span class=\"\"> food packaging is undergoing some interesting developments.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này liệt kê các nhu cầu và mối quan tâm mới của người tiêu dùng (công nghệ,</span><span class=\"\"> lãng phí,</span><span class=\"\"> sức khỏe),</span><span class=\"\"> vốn là những lý do thúc đẩy sự thay đổi trong ngành bao bì.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Section 3: Packaging that can be consumed with its contents</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 3.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> &#8220;</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Edible packaging</strong><span class=\"\"> has been proposed&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> KFC&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> edible coffee-cup.</span><span class=\"\"> Made from a </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">hard cookie</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> Stonyfield Organic&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> edible food wrappers&#8230;</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">skin has no flavor and can be rinsed and eaten</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Toàn bộ đoạn này tập trung vào các loại bao bì có thể ăn được (edible) cùng với thực phẩm bên trong như bánh quy,</span><span class=\"\"> gelatin hay vỏ làm từ tinh bột khoai tây.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Section 4: Packaging that allows consumers to use more of the product</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 4.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> &#8220;&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">nonstick packaging,</span><span class=\"\"> which can </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">eliminate the 3 to 15 percent of sauces left inside</strong><span class=\"\"> traditional bottles&#8230;</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">Liquiglide</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> allows viscous matter to </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">slide off easily</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này giới thiệu công nghệ chống dính giúp người dùng lấy sạch phần nước sốt còn sót lại trong chai,</span><span class=\"\"> tức là sử dụng được nhiều sản phẩm hơn so với bao bì cũ.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Section 5: Packaging that indicates when food is beginning to go rotten</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 5.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> &#8220;&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">detect and later prevent food from </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">spoiling</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> tiny embedded </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">sensors</strong><span class=\"\"> to first detect&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> nanotechnology&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> dedicated to making electronic sensors.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này nói về bao bì thông minh có cảm biến giúp nhận biết khi thực phẩm bắt đầu hư hỏng (rotten/spoiling) thay vì chỉ dựa vào hạn sử dụng ghi trên nhãn.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Section 6: Packaging that vanishes or decomposes quickly</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> &#8220;Another emerging technology is </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">packaging that disappears</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> water-soluble bags&#8230;</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">dissolves</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> seaweed that ‘will </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">wither at the same rate as its content</strong><span class=\"\">’.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tiêu đề này khớp hoàn toàn với nội dung về các loại túi hòa tan hoặc bao bì từ rong biển tự héo và biến mất khi không còn sử dụng.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Section 7: Packaging that doesn’t take up a lot of space</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 7.</span></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Super-compressed packaging</strong> serves the increasing number of city dwellers who generally have <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">tiny kitchens and no storage room</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn cuối nói về các loại bao bì siêu nén, chiếm ít diện tích, phù hợp với người sống ở đô thị có không gian nhỏ.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fdae2616-d9f7-42c2-919f-5ce968a16ad1', '29a7a4c4-0b18-421f-ab17-20af8c349efd', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-33', '<p>Complete the sentences below</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWOO WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Driverless vehicle competition</strong></span></p>
<p>Undergraduates from both the engineering school and the {computer science} department can definitely take part in the project.</p>
<p>The automated vehicles will have to avoid obstacles such as {rocks}</p>
<p>The tutor mentions one vehicle which used technology such as {video cameras}, laser, and laptops to measure its surroundings.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a tutor talking to a group of students about a project to build a driverless vehicle. First you have some time to look at questions 31 to 40. Now listen carefully and answer questions 31 to forty.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span data-path-to-node=\"5,0\"><strong>Lecturer:</strong> Hello everyone. I have an exciting announcement to make. The university has decided to enter an international competition next year, and we are going to need some enthusiastic undergraduates to help us with the project. The competition is to make an automated vehicle—a kind of robot—that will be able to move quickly and accurately on its own. All the vehicles will then enter a race which will take place here in the US. So t</span><span data-path-to-node=\"5,2\"><span class=\"citation-593\">he engineering school will be collaborating with the </span><strong><span class=\"citation-593\">(31) computer science</span></strong><span class=\"citation-593\"> department and possibly the automotive design department, although that&#8217;s yet to be confirmed.What they have to do is try to design an automated vehicle which will be able to complete the course. To give you an idea of how tough this race is, one vehicle last year only managed 12 kilometers of the 280-kilometer stretch of California desert that forms the racetrack. </span></span><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjzsNuUiJWRAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQgA4\"></button></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>Lecturer:</strong> The vehicles in the race must cover the whole distance without a human driver and quite autonomously identify and steer around corners and avoid unexpected hazards, things like <strong>(32) rocks</strong> for example. It&#8217;s a challenging task because there are lots of obstacles of this kind along the route.As I said, in last year&#8217;s event, the most successful vehicle only drove 12 km, then its team decided to deactivate it because it had gotten too near a cliff. In the race held earlier this year, there still wasn&#8217;t a winner, but they did much better and there was one design which we will be analyzing carefully in seminars. Its strength was in its on-board technology. That particular vehicle  built a three-dimensional picture of its surroundings using <strong>(33) video cameras</strong> and lasers. It was equipped with seven laptop computers which analyze the incoming information 10 times a second, and it drove along at a comfortable 55 km per hour.The design details have been published, so we hope to learn from them and go on to make ours even better for next year&#8217;s competition. The competition is open to all universities and there&#8217;s a prize of $2 million for the winner.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>Lecturer:</strong>But it&#8217;s really about more than that. The sponsors are hoping to see innovative design ideas that they can transfer into commercial production.You&#8217;ll get a lot out of this project as well in terms of working as a team and broadening your knowledge of the subject. The key to winning is unlikely to be anything to do with what the vehicle looks like;  <strong>(34) The purpose of holding the race is to find useful new design features (C)</strong>. Programming skills will decide who eventually wins first prize. <strong>(35) The design will need technological expertise in this area above all (A: The software design)</strong>, and that&#8217;s what the team who work on the project will need to focus on. I&#8217;ll be handing out some scientific reports about this year&#8217;s vehicle shortly. It&#8217;s interesting to read that even after months and months of planning, building, and trials, many of the teams were amazed that the vehicles did what they wanted them to do at all, because so many things can go wrong on the day. So even though no vehicle actually completed the course, they were pleased they got as far as they did. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong>Lecturer:</strong> If any of you are interested, this is the plan of action:</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Firstly, at the beginning of May, we’ll be scheduling an introductory <strong>(37) seminar</strong> about the project.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Later in the month (Late May), we’ll be asking you to submit a short essay letting us know why you feel you should be chosen, and tell us about any particular <strong>(38) skills</strong> that you have.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Then in June, we’re organizing a trip to a factory…</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">Then at the beginning of the next semester in September, we thought we’d hold a weekend workshop to share <strong>(39) ideas</strong> and see computer aided design demonstrations.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\">The following month (January), we’ll choose the <strong>(40) team</strong> and start work in earnest.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 4. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('de6435fa-2373-4420-adfa-926402f86f82', '29a7a4c4-0b18-421f-ab17-20af8c349efd', 'radio', 'Question 34-36', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Interest students in careers in industry"}, {"content": "Help provide finance for universities"}, {"content": "Find useful new design features"}], "question": " The purpose of holding the race is to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "The software design"}, {"content": "Good, solid construction"}, {"content": "Sophisticated mechanisms"}], "question": "The tutor says success will depend on"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "Were so easy to design"}, {"content": "Were as successful as they were"}, {"content": "Took such a short time to construct"}], "question": "This year’s competitors were surprised that the vehicles"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4cc13323-0c50-44e1-a816-25097932c686', '680fcb0b-abb0-4051-9c0e-4592be1568de', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–20', '', '<p><span class="fontstyle0">Write the correct letter, </span><strong><span class="fontstyle2">A–G</span></strong><span class="fontstyle0">, in boxes 14–20 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle2"><strong>NB</strong> </span><span class="fontstyle0">You may use any letter more than once.</span> </p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "an example of how farmers in one country are now using satellite data to determine fertiliser use", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a reference to climate change and its effects", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a reference to the effect on the soil of using too much fertiliser", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an example of information that will be shared between different countries", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "a mention of the country which is the leader in agricultural technology", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a description of an innovation in satellite imaging which requires further study", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "evidence of the cost effectiveness of using satellite technology in agriculture", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. C — {an example of how farmers in one country are now using satellite data to determine fertiliser use}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Five times a year, for example, a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">French cereal-growers'' co-operative called Sevépi purchases satellite data and makes it available to its members in the form of maps of their fields</strong>... For each zone, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"213\">one of about 50 fertiliser formulas is recommended</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Farmers in one country\" được minh họa bằng hợp tác xã trồng ngũ cốc của Pháp tên là Sevépi (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">French co-operative</em>). Việc họ dùng bản đồ dữ liệu vệ tinh để nhận khuyến nghị 1 trong 50 công thức phân bón cho từng vùng đất chính là ví dụ cụ thể cho việc dùng dữ liệu vệ tinh để xác định lượng phân bón (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"311\">determine fertiliser use</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. D — {a reference to climate change and its effects}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...reckons the amount of monitored farmland will increase <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">as weather patterns change and farmers can no longer rely on the past as a guide to the future. When confounded by the yield variations that these new weather patterns will bring</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"weather patterns change\" (các mô hình thời tiết thay đổi) và \"new weather patterns\" (các kiểu thời tiết mới) chính là cách viết khác của biến đổi khí hậu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">climate change</strong>). Hệ quả/tác động của nó (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"216\">its effects</em>) được nhắc đến là việc nông dân không thể dựa vào kinh nghiệm quá khứ và năng suất cây trồng sẽ bị biến động thất thường (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"350\">yield variations</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. E — {a reference to the effect on the soil of using too much fertiliser}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...proving useful for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">study of fields with declining productivity</strong> in the province of Saskatchewan. <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">Overkill with nitrate fertilisers</strong> (which are also a source of greenhouse gases) <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">appears partly responsible</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Using too much fertiliser\" (dùng quá nhiều phân bón) đồng nghĩa với từ \"Overkill with nitrate fertilisers\" (lạm dụng/dùng quá tải phân đạm). Hệ quả của việc này tác động lên đất đai (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">effect on the soil</em>) được đề cập rõ ràng là làm cho các cánh đồng bị suy giảm năng suất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"284\">declining productivity</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. G — {an example of information that will be shared between different countries}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_24de963377adc1f2-38\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“As a consequence, the charitable trust World Agroforestry Centre, in the city of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">Nairobi, in Kenya</strong><span class=\"citation-756\">, has begun to build up a catalogue of the radiation patterns derived from around 100,000 samples of </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"211\"><span class=\"citation-756\">African soils</span></strong><span class=\"citation-756\">... Once </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\"><span class=\"citation-756 citation-end-756\">passed on to the International Centre for Tropical Agriculture, based in Colombia, Sout<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>h America</strong>, it is intended that the information be <span class=\"citation-755\">used to build a database called the ‘Digital Soil Map’. When ready, </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"438\"><span class=\"citation-755\">this will provide farmers with free forecasts... across farmland in a number of countries in Africa</span></strong><span class=\"citation-755\">.”</span></em><span class=\"citation-755 citation-end-755\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_24de963377adc1f2-39\" data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-754\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-754 citation-end-754\"> Đoạn này mô tả một <sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span>chuỗi chia sẻ thông tin xuyên quốc gia và châu lục: Dữ liệu đất thu thập ở Kenya (Châu Phi) được chuyển giao (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">passed on</em>) cho một trung tâm quốc tế ở Colombia (Nam Mỹ), sau đó cơ sở dữ liệu này lại được dùng để cung cấp dự báo miễn phí cho nông dân ở nhiều quốc gia khác tại Châu Phi (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"315\">a number of countries in Africa</em>). Đây là ví dụ hoàn hảo cho \"information shared between different countries\".</p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. D — {a mention of the country which is the leader in agricultural technology}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">France is the pioneer in this sort of surveillance. More farmland is analysed by satellite there than in any other country</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"The leader\" (người dẫn đầu/tiên phong) đồng nghĩa với từ \"pioneer\". Quốc gia dẫn đầu về công nghệ giám sát nông nghiệp bằng vệ tinh này được gọi tên trực tiếp là nước Pháp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"186\">France</strong>), nơi có lượng đất nông nghiệp được phân tích bằng vệ tinh nhiều hơn bất kỳ quốc gia nào khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. F — {a description of an innovation in satellite imaging which requires further study}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_24de963377adc1f2-40\" data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“‘Our satellites are the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">first commercial satellites to include the Red-Edge band</strong> of the light spec<span class=\"citation-753\">trum, which is sensitive to changes in chlorophyll content. </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\"><span class=\"citation-753\">More research will be necessary to realise the full potential of the Red-Edge band</span></strong><span class=\"citation-753\">...’”</span></em><span class=\"citation-753 citation-end-753\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_24de963377adc1f2-41\" data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-752\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-752 citation-end-752\"> \"An innovation in satellite imaging\" (một cải tiến/đột phá trong hìn<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span>h ảnh vệ tinh) chính là dải quang phổ viền đỏ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">Red-Edge band</strong>) lần đầu tiên được đưa vào vệ tinh thương mại. Đại diện công ty khẳng định dải quang phổ này cần phải được nghiên cứu thêm nhiều nữa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"275\">More research will be necessary / requires further study</strong>) để khai thác hết tiềm năng.</p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. B — {evidence of the cost effectiveness of using satellite technology in agriculture}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The service usually <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">costs less than US$15 per hectare</strong> for a handful of readings a year, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">can increase yields by as much as 10%</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Cost effectiveness\" (hiệu quả về mặt chi phí - tức là chi phí bỏ ra thấp nhưng thu lại lợi ích cao). Đoạn B đưa ra minh chứng bằng số liệu rất cụ thể (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">evidence</em>): chi phí rất rẻ (dưới 15 USD/hecta) nhưng lại giúp tăng năng suất cây trồng lên tới 10% (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"263\">increase yields by 10%</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3d637741-72fd-460c-b687-71eb46ecd06d', 'a515df3a-24ef-4406-b3e8-a201b8dd852f', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Elephant research in Amboseli</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Methodology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The elephant population has been studied for almost forty years.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Records of many elephants’ dates of birth and also of their {mother} have been kept.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Play-back of elephant calls and DNA analysis were also used.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Findings</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The social system of elephants has many {layers}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Co-operation</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Two elephants worked together to get food using a {rope}<strong>.</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Flexibility</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Some moved to a new area when there was a lack of {rain}<strong>.</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Emotion</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>They may move the {bones} of another elephant after death.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Intelligence</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Their brain {weight} is quite high in comparison with that of their body.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Male elephants pass through periods of virility called ‘musth’</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The way they {walk} is one obvious change.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p><strong>Elephants need to live a long time.</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Older males make better mates: older females recognize {danger}<strong>.</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What still needs to be discovered</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>How elephants use smell-difficult to study this in the {wild}<strong>.</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>How {sensitive} elephants are to one another</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-heading"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: ELEPHANT RESEARCH IN AMBOSELI</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Caroline Stewart:</strong> Good morning, my name is Caroline Stewart and I’d like to give you an overview of the research we’ve been carrying out to learn more about the elephants living in the Amboseli National Park in Kenya.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Let me start by telling you a little about the methodology we use. We’ve been studying this population of elephants for nearly 40 years and we’ve collected a wealth of information about individual elephants. We now have a database of 2,500 elephants from the area and we know the month and year of their birth as well as who was the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"333\">(31) mother</strong></span> of each one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">More recently, one of my colleagues has been examining the pattern of elephant relationships within and between the families in more detail. He’s done this by using audio equipment to record and then play back the calls that are made by the elephants, and in addition to that, for some time we’ve been using DNA analysis to investigate these relationships.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">The findings were significant. For example, for a long time we’d suspected that elephants live in a very complex social system and one thing we found from our research is that this social system is made up of a large number of different<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">(32) layers</strong>,</span> not just parent and child but also brother and sister and so on.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_f63baa2bf1ba8858-64\" data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-224 citation-end-224\">Another important discovery was that elephants can be very cooperative—as much as chimps in fact.</span> We conducted an experiment in which two of the elephants brought food within reach by pulling simultaneously on the ends of a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"224\">(33) rope</strong>.</span> It was a surprise even to us that they managed to do it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Another finding was just how flexible elephants can be. They may live in smaller or larger groups depending on environmental conditions. So for example, an adult female and her calves might leave their larger groups for days or weeks. A good example of this was two years ago when there was not enough<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"302\">(34) rain</strong></span>; many left the herd and moved to new areas in order to survive.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">We also discovered that elephants can show emotion. For example, when an elephant dies, the others may stroke and rearrange the<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">(35) bones</strong>,</span> although why they do it is still a mystery.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Elephants are very intelligent creatures. We’ve dedicated a whole chapter to this in our new book as the findings are so important. For example, when we looked at the elephant’s brain, we found that its<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">(36) weight</strong></span> was quite high compared with that of its body, which is significant.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_f63baa2bf1ba8858-65\" data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"citation-223 citation-end-223\">Early on in the research, we discovered that bull elephants, i.e., males, go through periods of significant change which is called “musth”.</span> This serves to advertise the male’s virility to other females, letting them know he’s healthy and would be a good father. But it also warns other males to stay away. One of the most obvious changes is in how they<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"353\">(37) walk</strong></span>, though there are others.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">However, one of our most important discoveries is that it is crucial for elephants to live for a long time. If you are a male, you probably won’t be a successful mate unless you do. If you are a female, the older and more experienced you are, the more likely it is that you’ll be aware of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"289\">(38) danger</strong> </span>when it approaches. For example, an elephant may be able to cope with one lion, but may have problems if there are three of them. Age helps elephants know when it’s best to walk away or to stand and fight.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">There’s a huge amount that’s still waiting to be discovered. For example, we know very little about the part that’s played in the life of elephants by their sense of smell, although we suspect that it must be important because this sense is very well developed. It’s very hard to conduct research in this area in the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"317\">(39) wild</strong></span> because there are so many variables involved.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Another area we know little about is illustrated by a time I observed a young elephant reaching out towards an electric fence. His mother’s whole body posture displayed alarm at the danger he was in. This is an example of how one elephant can be <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"246\">(40) sensitive</strong> </span>towards the feelings or situation of another, but we don’t know how much it happens.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6fb0cdd7-85b9-404a-9f90-2f36faeb6911', 'de8e13ca-75a0-430e-8ef4-9a7c3b1083b1', 'matrix', 'Questions 14-18', NULL, '<p>Which section contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter,<strong> A-G</strong></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a species that indicates to its young to move to a place where they are less visible", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "an instance where sound is used to help an animal escape", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "reature that can use camouflage to match a range of different backgrounds", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a claim that the majority of animals disguise themselves in some way", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "examples of animals that use camouflage to look like plants", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. A species that indicates to its young to move to a place where they are less visible.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">C</strong>, dòng cuối: “…when the chicks land they are usually highly conspicuous, and their <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">parents try to signal to them to move to a safe location</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “signal to them to move” tương ứng với “indicates to its young to move”. Loài chim Tawny Frogmouth (Cú muỗi mỏ quặp) cha mẹ sẽ ra hiệu cho con non di chuyển đến chỗ an toàn (ít bị lộ hơn).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. An instance where sound is used to help an animal escape.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: G</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">G</strong>, dòng 4-5: “…in the case of the chameleon gecko the tail bones actually rub against one another, so <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">it squeaks</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Loài tắc kè Chameleon gecko khi rụng đuôi, chiếc đuôi đó sẽ phát ra tiếng kêu “squeaks” (chít chít) để thu hút sự chú ý của kẻ thù, giúp nó trốn thoát.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. A creature that can use camouflage to match a range of different backgrounds.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">D</strong>, dòng 1-3: “…some animals, such as the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">cuttlefish</strong>, have evolved an <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">adaptable disguise</strong>… change its colour, Pattern and texture to match its surroundings…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mực nang (cuttlefish) có khả năng thay đổi màu sắc và vân da ngay lập tức để phù hợp với nhiều môi trường khác nhau (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">adaptable disguise</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. A claim that the majority of animals disguise themselves in some way.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">A</strong>, dòng đầu tiên: “<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">Most species use camouflage to some extent</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “Most species” đồng nghĩa với “the majority of animals”. Tất cả các loài đều ngụy trang ở một mức độ nào đó để sinh tồn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Examples of animals that use camouflage to look like plants.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">B</strong>, dòng 2-4: “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">stick and leaf insects</strong> have evolved complex camouflage… Many have the texture of sticks or dry leaves, while others imitate living foliage…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các loài côn trùng lá và côn trùng que bắt chước hình dạng của cành cây hoặc lá khô để ẩn mình.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ae328871-cb85-4819-b6d4-c806ba39bc1b', '2c3ad16d-88b5-497f-a8ce-bc9b03da1423', 'fillup', 'Questions 1 – 4 ', '<p>Label the diagram below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 1–4 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," width="686" height="572" loading="lazy"></p>
<p>{hopper}</p>
<p>{cylinder}</p>
<p>{funnel}</p>
<p>{spikes}</p>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. hopper</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;This allowed seed to pass evenly from the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">hopper</strong> above to a funnel below.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong sơ đồ máy gieo hạt, cái phễu lớn ở phía trên dùng để chứa hạt giống chính là &#8220;hopper&#8221;.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. cylinder</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 6.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;In his device, as the main wheels of the drill turned, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">cylinder</strong> rotated against a spring-held tongue.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là bộ phận hình trụ xoay tròn khi bánh xe di chuyển để điều tiết hạt giống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. funnel</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;from the hopper above to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">funnel</strong> below. From here, the seed was directed&#8230; into three channels.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hạt giống từ phễu chứa đi xuống một cái phễu nhỏ hơn (funnel) trước khi vào các rãnh đất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. spikes</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 10.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Spikes</strong> at the back of the machine then turned the soil over to immediately cover the seeds.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bộ phận ở phía sau máy có nhiệm vụ lấp đất lên hạt giống chính là các &#8220;spikes&#8221; (đinh nhọn/răng cào).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8e12db7b-fe35-4c0d-8f3f-1819f9bbd72e', '680fcb0b-abb0-4051-9c0e-4592be1568de', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21 and 22', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters, <strong>A–E</strong>.</p>
<p>Write the correct letters in boxes 21 and 22 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>companies obtain information directly from satellites? </p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A Sevépi"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B Infoterra"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D RapidEye"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E World Agroforestry Centre"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. B. Infoterra</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...according to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">Infoterra</strong> (a subsidiary of EADS Astrium), <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">the firm that is France''s largest provider of such information, supplying data to companies such as Sevépi</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Infoterra là nhà cung cấp thông tin vệ tinh lớn nhất nước Pháp và họ là bên cung cấp, bán lại dữ liệu (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">supplying data</em>) cho các công ty khác như Sevépi. Điều này có nghĩa Infoterra là đơn vị trực tiếp xử lý và lấy nguồn từ vệ tinh của tập đoàn mẹ (EADS Astrium).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. D. RapidEye</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E &amp; F):</strong> * <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">Đoạn E:</em> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">“And according to <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">RapidEye, a German satellite operator</strong>...”</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,1,0,0\"><em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đoạn F:</em> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"9\">Our satellites</strong> are the first commercial satellites to include the Red-Edge band...”</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc định nghĩa rõ ràng RapidEye là một <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">nhà vận hành vệ tinh của Đức</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">a German satellite operator</em>). Ở đoạn F, đại diện của họ cũng tự tin khẳng định \"Các vệ tinh của chúng tôi\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">Our satellites</em>). Là bên sở hữu và vận hành vệ tinh, RapidEye chắc chắn có được thông tin trực tiếp từ vệ tinh của chính mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('16abb38c-0b3a-45b4-af80-e9eb2f023c5d', '680fcb0b-abb0-4051-9c0e-4592be1568de', 'fillup', 'Questions 23–26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 23–26 on your answer sheet.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Initially, orbiting satellites are used to measure {electromagnetic radiation} coming from farmland.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>{Henri Douche} believes that confusion about irregular weather will cause more farmers to</p>
<p>use satellite technology.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>As a result of satellite technology, it may become possible to insure against the risk</p>
<p>of {crop failure} .</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In Africa, much of the soil suffers from the loss of {nutrients}. </p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. electromagnetic radiation — {Initially, orbiting satellites are used to measure electromagnetic radiation coming from farmland.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Precise prescriptions for growing crops can be obtained quickly... by calculating the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">amount of electromagnetic radiation reflected from agricultural land</strong>. <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">The data is collected by orbiting satellites</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói về việc các vệ tinh quay quanh quỹ đạo (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">orbiting satellites</em>) được dùng để đo lường cái gì đến từ đất canh tác (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">coming from farmland</em>). Bài đọc viết rằng dữ liệu được thu thập bởi vệ tinh bằng cách tính toán lượng bức xạ điện từ phản xạ từ đất nông nghiệp (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"279\">reflected from agricultural land</em>). Từ cần điền là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"329\">electromagnetic radiation</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Henri Douche — {Henri Douche believes that confusion about irregular weather will cause more farmers to use satellite technology.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Moreover, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">Henri Douche</strong>, head of Infoterra''s agriculture sales in Toulouse, reckons the amount of monitored farmland will increase as weather patterns change... <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">When confounded by the yield variations that these new weather patterns will bring, even farmers who are afraid of new technology will sign up</strong>, he says.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Confusion\" (sự bối rối/hoang mang) đồng nghĩa với từ \"confounded\". \"Irregular weather\" (thời tiết thất thường) tương ứng với cụm \"new weather patterns / yield variations\". Người đưa ra nhận định rằng sự biến động này sẽ khiến nhiều nông dân đăng ký sử dụng công nghệ vệ tinh hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"293\">will sign up / use satellite technology</em>) chính là ông <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"347\">Henri Douche</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. crop failure — {As a result of satellite technology, it may become possible to insure against the risk of crop failure.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...insurance companies are also studying satellite data with a view to <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">selling insurance policies</strong> to governments of famine-prone countries <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">that might be threatened by crop failure</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Insure against the risk of...\" (bảo hiểm cho những rủi ro về...) tương ứng với hành động bán các chính sách bảo hiểm (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">selling insurance policies</em>) khi gặp mối đe dọa từ điều gì. Mối đe dọa/Rủi ro được nhắc đến ở đây là nạn mất mùa, thất thu mùa màng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"263\">crop failure</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. nutrients — {In Africa, much of the soil suffers from the loss of nutrients.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In Africa, where <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">many soils have become badly depleted of nutrients</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Much of the soil\" (phần lớn đất đai) đồng nghĩa với \"many soils\". Cụm từ \"suffers from the loss of...\" (chịu tổn hại do mất đi/thiếu hụt cái gì) đồng nghĩa hoàn toàn với cụm \"become badly depleted of...\" (bị suy kiệt/cạn kiệt nghiêm trọng cái gì). Yếu tố bị mất đi ở đây là chất dinh dưỡng trong đất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"314\">nutrients</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('128ff9c7-8af5-4585-9f75-f00d3c895cdc', '29a7a4c4-0b18-421f-ab17-20af8c349efd', 'fillup', 'Question 37-40', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
