INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e13fcaef-569f-4396-a708-21a029915ff3', 'ff080e73-4963-4496-9426-124ad166aa90', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "seen as an opportunity to learn."}, {"content": "predicted and minimised."}, {"content": "avoided at all costs."}], "question": "Arthur feels that when starting a business, mistakes should be"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "sometimes reduce people''s chances of success."}, {"content": "be increased by reading self-help books."}, {"content": "ensure good results on business courses."}], "question": "Recent American studies found that confidence will"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "listen to their colleagues’ advice."}, {"content": "get professional help when things go wrong."}, {"content": "remain concentrated on their aims."}], "question": "The American studies recommended that new entrepreneurs"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "He relied on what he already knew."}, {"content": "He hired an expert to take care of it."}, {"content": "He realised its importance too late."}], "question": "What does Arthur say about his own experience of marketing?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "They are ambitious for their company."}, {"content": "They can deal with difficult people."}, {"content": "They earn the respect of their workforce."}], "question": "What does Arthur think Is an important quality shared by good leaders?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "He advises being cautions."}, {"content": "He favours a long-term view."}, {"content": "He believes it is financially advantageous."}], "question": "What does Arthur say about taking risks?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SECTION 2</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Arthur:</strong> Good evening, my name is Arthur Jones. I&#8217;m very glad to have this opportunity to speak to you over the radio. The host asked me to give a talk about my experience of starting my own business. I can&#8217;t say my business is successful, but there are some things that I want to share with you which I think will be helpful if you want to start your own company.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">I&#8217;ve talked to many young people and they told me that they are afraid of making mistakes when they start their business. What I want to say is that mistakes are very common, especially when you do something new.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(11) Mistakes can actually show you where you need to improve, so you can take actions about them and use the chance to learn new methods (A: seen as an opportunity to learn)</strong>. </span></span>This is a very important attitude you should have. Besides, most mistakes are not that fatal; don&#8217;t be too anxious when they occur.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Next, I want to go on to talk about self-confidence, which is quite important in achieving business success. Being self-confident means that you can have faith in yourself and what you do. Self-confidence can be gained through hard work, even playing sports.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> However, <strong>(12) sometimes self-confidence may make you ignore problems and even cause failure (A: sometimes reduce people&#8217;s chances of success)</strong>.</span> Business leaders should remain calm and not take impulsive actions.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">I know that when people start their business, they have confusions. They don&#8217;t know how they can be more professional. They read business journals or watch related videos, but these don&#8217;t seem to help sometimes. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">My suggestion is that <strong>(13) instead of aimlessly trying many new things, they should always be committed to their goal (C: remain concentrated on their aims)</strong>. </span>As long as they stick to it, they will not be easily distracted or confused by other things, and they are sure to get better.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We will all meet difficulties, especially at the beginning. We can&#8217;t always rely on ourselves to solve all the problems. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(14) I had a problem with marketing earlier this year; luckily I found an expert to help me deal with it (B: hired an expert to take care of it)</strong>. </span>So there&#8217;s always a way, but we should know how and when to seek help from these people.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Business leaders have different kinds of styles. Some are very good at public speaking, others are very down-to-earth and have strong executive skills.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> But in general, <strong>(15) they should be able to win the respect from their employees (C: earn the respect of their workforce)</strong>, so that they can carry out their orders more easily.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are times when a company might face risks. During such times, leaders will need to take prompt actions and they can&#8217;t always plan for the distant future. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(16) Leaders should analyze and deal with the risks with caution (A: advises being cautious)</strong>.</span> If they bear this in mind, there is always a way out.</p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">\n<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Arthur:</strong> At the beginning of my business, I experimented with quite a few strategies, hoping to find out the best solution for my business. Here is what I found. At first, my company wanted to work out prices for the products and make them realistic; however, prices are always changing, so they can&#8217;t be fixed.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">Another thing I always keep in mind is that leaders must <strong>(17/18) stay committed to their jobs (C: being committed to it)</strong>.</span> Without enough commitment, you may easily give up when problems happen. I have some friends whose businesses didn&#8217;t survive during difficult times; it wasn&#8217;t because they were stupid, it was just a lack of commitment<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">. I can&#8217;t always be sure that my products or services are better than my competitors, but I <strong>(17/18) pay attention to details (D: paying attention to detail)</strong> and try to improve all the little things, as they can actually make a big difference.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You might worry that you don&#8217;t have a very clear and sophisticated business strategy. Personally, I don&#8217;t think it&#8217;s a problem because you will be changing them all the time anyway. In terms of support at any stage, we do need support from others to back up our business. The support can really make a difference. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">Before I started my business, <strong>(19/20) my family helped me a lot, both financially and mentally (A: family support)</strong>.</span> There were also people who gave me advice on how to run businesses successfully; however, these advice and ideas were not so practical to me, so I didn&#8217;t really use them. Looking back, I felt lucky that I followed my own way of thinking. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">Also, I was short of funds back then and <strong>(19/20) I loaned money from the bank to start my company (B: getting a loan from a bank)</strong>. I was grateful for that.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">That&#8217;s what I want to share in today&#8217;s program. If you have any questions for me, please send it to my email&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1cfb1a40-4549-4a17-9860-7482b24ca122', 'ff080e73-4963-4496-9426-124ad166aa90', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17–18', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>things does Arthur say people should focus on when developing their business idea?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "making sure the idea is original", "correct": false}, {"option": "offering a better deal than competitors", "correct": false}, {"option": "being committed to it", "correct": true}, {"option": "paying attention to detail", "correct": true}, {"option": "fixing realistic prices", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9da579c0-e046-475a-8877-5332569641d7', 'ff080e73-4963-4496-9426-124ad166aa90', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19–20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>things does Arthur say helped him get his business started?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "family support", "correct": true}, {"option": "getting a loan from a bank", "correct": true}, {"option": "good business advice", "correct": false}, {"option": "a favourable economic climate", "correct": false}, {"option": "an effective approach to business", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f2eecc3e-7400-4537-9c13-4758b5bb9eb0', '8f9eec03-5894-4b7d-9b5a-ae64fd8c45a5', 'fillup', 'Questions 20–23', '<p>Complete the summary.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<h3 data-start="687" data-end="742">Plant communication research in Israel and Scotland</h3>
<p data-start="744" data-end="1191">Plants may send messages via their {roots} according to Ariel Novoplansky of Ben-Gurion University in Israel. In one study, Novoplansky’s team planted rows of garden peas, and created conditions like a {drought} around the first plant in each row. The plants responded by closing the tiny holes on their leaf surfaces, known as pores. They then appeared to signal to other plants nearby, causing them to respond in a similar way.</p>
<p data-start="1193" data-end="1629">Research at the University of Aberdeen in Scotland, meanwhile, has focused on the networks of {fungi} which connect the plants beneath the soil. These structures, which extract sugars from the plants and supply them with phosphorus and nitrogen, also seem to play a key role in plant communication. Experiments involving broad bean and plant-eating insects called {aphids} have also produced some interesting results.</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Plants may send messages via their {roots}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…distress signals can be passed through the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">plants’ roots</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. …created conditions like a {drought} around the first plant…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…subjected the first in each row to conditions similar to those experienced in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">drought</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. …focused on the networks of {fungi} which connect the plants…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…labyrinths of hair-like <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">fungi</strong> that occur around the roots of most plants.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. …plant-eating insects called {aphids} have also produced some interesting results.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…broad bean plants were infested with <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">aphids</strong> – small herbivorous insects…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('348a67dd-f964-4398-9805-f2a987865d07', 'd348c5ae-4a25-40cf-b462-67f67dc00aa5', 'fillup', 'Questions 6–13', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p><strong>February 1861: Storm warning service</strong><br>• FitzRoy received weather reports produced by ships using reliable {instruments}<br>• simultaneous weather reports were taken daily<br>• storm warnings were telegraphed to  {ports }  along the shore<br>• signals for ships were displayed using raised { flags  }<br>• the storm warning service was the greatest development in sea safety since the  {lifeboat}   was introduced</p>
<p><strong>August 1861: Public weather forecasting service</strong><br>• very popular in The Times newspaper<br>• frequently used by the English Queen for safe trips to a favourite { island  }<br>• FitzRoy’s forecasts were popular with fishermen but not with boat  {owners}<br>• in modern times FitzRoy’s  {name}   is used for a marine area<br>• FitzRoy produced a  {book }  which was respected by the scientific community</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. instruments</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…FitzRoy’s innovation was to issue ships with standardised <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">instruments</strong> which allowed for accurate weather reports.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để có báo cáo chính xác, FitzRoy đã cung cấp cho các con tàu những thiết bị/dụng cụ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">instruments</strong>) đo đạc tiêu chuẩn thay vì để họ dùng các đồ dùng không đồng nhất.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. ports</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…FitzRoy could telegraph warnings to <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">ports</strong> on the coast…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các cảnh báo về bão sắp tới được gửi bằng điện báo từ London đến các cảng biển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">ports</strong>) dọc theo bờ biển để thông báo kịp thời cho tàu bè.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. flags</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…where an ingenious system of <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">flags</strong> was hoisted up high for passing ships to read.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tại các cảng, người ta sử dụng một hệ thống các lá cờ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">flags</strong>) kéo lên cao để các tàu đi ngang qua có thể nhận diện tín hiệu nguy hiểm từ xa.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. lifeboat</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “This represented the biggest advance in shipping safety after the introduction of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">lifeboat</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hệ thống của FitzRoy được đánh giá là bước tiến quan trọng nhất trong an toàn hàng hải kể từ sau khi thuyền cứu sinh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">lifeboat</strong>) ra đời.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. island</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…to get a forecast for the sea crossing over the Solent to an <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">island</strong> which she liked to visit…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nữ hoàng Anh thường xem dự báo để di chuyển an toàn đến hòn đảo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">island</strong>) yêu thích của bà ở lepas bờ biển phía Nam.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. owners</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “The <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">owners</strong> of fishing vessels, however, were not supportive of FitzRoy’s forecasts…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong khi ngư dân ủng hộ vì an toàn, thì các chủ tàu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">owners</strong>) lại ghét dự báo này vì nó thường làm trì hoãn lịch trình di chuyển của tàu, gây thiệt hại kinh tế.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. name</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “…with the honour of an area of sea being given his <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">name</strong> in the shipping forecast…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để vinh danh FitzRoy, tên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">name</strong>) của ông đã được đặt cho một vùng biển trong các bản tin dự báo hàng hải hiện đại.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. book</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “…late in his life he published a <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">book</strong> about weather forecasting which was recognized by other scientists to be well ahead of its time.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cuối đời, ông đã để lại di sản là một cuốn sách (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">book</strong>) về dự báo thời tiết, tác phẩm được các nhà khoa học sau này thừa nhận là vượt xa thời đại bấy giờ.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a80314e3-404a-48df-915d-27c8706101ac', 'ce4ef4e6-ff7e-44b9-9971-b6987f01c5ad', 'matching', 'Questions 21–26', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-H</strong>, next to questions 21-26.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Subject of Experiments</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Steam engine {B too difficult}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Breakfast cereals {G cheap to do}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Bouncing balls {F useful practice for maths}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Making paper {A very boring}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Tie-dying {H takes longer than usual to do}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Glue from milk {E immediate results}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A very boring"}, {"optionText": "B too difficult"}, {"optionText": "C specialised equipment needed"}, {"optionText": "D very expensive"}, {"optionText": "E immediate results"}, {"optionText": "F useful practice for maths"}, {"optionText": "G cheap to do"}, {"optionText": "H takes longer than usual to do"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 3</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Hi Magda, how was your placement?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> It went really well. The kids really enjoyed the science I did with them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> So did mine. I think they found it very motivating.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Yes, the program we had to teach was much better than the old-style science experiments we did at school.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Yes, though I don’t understand why the children should have to build a model of a <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">steam engine</strong>.</span> I tried it with the kids but I couldn’t get it to work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Me neither. And it really shows <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">(21) it’s hard to get any real results [Đáp án B: too difficult]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Yes, and it’s usually the children’s parents rather than the kids themselves who favour that type of experiment. So what experiments did you do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Well, one day a discussion started in class about <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">breakfast cereals</strong></span>, about which one was best. One child then said that we should test them in class.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> That’s a nice idea.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Yes, and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">(22) it wasn’t expensive [Đáp án G: cheap to do]</strong>.</span></span> We brought four different brands of cereal and had everyone evaluate them for taste, appearance and sogginess in milk.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Another experiment we did—the sports teacher’s idea actually—was to spend a morning seeing how high various<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">bouncing balls</strong> </span>bounced. For example, do new tennis balls bounce higher than old ones?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> And I guess you got some interesting data?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> We did, and they had to make a chart to plot the results<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">. <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">(23) It really improved their grasp of charts and graphs and calculation [Đáp án F: useful practice for maths]</strong>.</span> Apparently, they’d had problems understanding the point of graphs in the past.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Did all your experiments work out OK?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Well, we had one lesson on<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">making paper</strong> </span>from grass. The children made a terrible mess in the classroom. Whatever they did didn&#8217;t work, and it wasn’t because it was difficult. I think it was because <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"206\">(24) it didn’t engage them at all [Đáp án A: very boring]</strong>.</span> It didn’t seem to motivate them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> My <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"10\">tie-dying</strong> experiment went well. They had to get a piece of material and twist it into a rope and then dye it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> But don’t you need to spend more than one lesson on that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Yes,<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">(25) we did it over three classes [Đáp án H: takes longer than usual to do]</strong>. </span></span>The children really loved it though.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> I guess the one experiment that everyone loved in my class was making <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">glue from milk</strong>.</span> I thought it would be a complete failure, but in fact it worked brilliantly. One reason I suspect is that <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">(26) they got feedback straight away [Đáp án E: immediate results]</strong></span>. Some children get really restless if they have to wait for anything interesting to happen.</p>\n<hr />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> I see you’ve got a diagram there for one of your experiments.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> Yes, it was an idea I got from the internet. It was very easy and straightforward to set up. The idea is to make a condenser to extract essences from plants.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> The <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">large container</strong>&#8216;s made of <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">metal</strong> right? <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">(27: D)</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> That’s right and it holds the hot water. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">And it has a <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">strainer</strong> which sits inside it. <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">(28: F)</strong></span> This is where you put the plant matter. We use plants like Rosemary as the essence you can extract is quite strong.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> So what’s the container right at the top?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> It’s made of glass, it’s where we put the ice. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">The glass container has a <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">drip tip</strong> at the bottom. <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">(29: G)</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> What’s that for?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> It’s where the essence collects.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Where does the essence go then?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Magda:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">Into the <strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">dish at the bottom</strong>. It’s made of <strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">pottery</strong>. <strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">(30: C)</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Stefan:</strong> Sounds good. I might try it with my class.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6b6143a7-6fa8-4eec-80d9-92b05cf8430a', 'c4743f7a-0642-44e7-b449-8bfc876472d1', 'radio', 'Questions 7–13', NULL, '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p dir="ltr">Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
</div>
</div>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "For steamboats to cross the Atlantic Ocean, engines which used fuel economically were needed"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Using paddle wheels guaranteed reliability on ocean crossings"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Savannah was much faster than a regular paddle steamer"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Brunel preferred designing railways to steamships"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Great Britain had more than one innovative feature"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The design of the riverboat Archimedes was widely admired"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Modern ships that cross the Atlantic use the same energy source as the early steamships"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. For steamboats to cross the Atlantic Ocean, engines which used fuel economically were needed.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Travelling under steam power alone would require engines to use less coal so the ship could stay at sea for several weeks.&#8221; (Đoạn 5).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để băng qua Đại Tây Dương, tàu cần động cơ dùng ít than hơn (tiết kiệm nhiên liệu/economically) để có thể duy trì trên biển nhiều tuần.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Using paddle wheels guaranteed reliability on ocean crossings.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;it was also necessary to replace paddle wheels as a source of power with something less affected by the rolling of the ship.&#8221; (Đoạn 5).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng bánh guồng (paddle wheels) bị ảnh hưởng bởi sự rung lắc của tàu, nên cần phải thay thế chúng để đảm bảo sự tin cậy. Do đó, nói bánh guồng &#8220;đảm bảo sự tin cậy&#8221; là sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. The Savannah was much faster than a regular paddle steamer.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 6 nhắc đến tàu Savannah là tàu đầu tiên kết hợp buồm và hơi nước để vượt đại dương.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">không hề so sánh</strong> tốc độ của tàu Savannah với các tàu hơi nước bánh guồng thông thường khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Brunel preferred designing railways to steamships.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Brunel&#8230; had already built the Great Western Railway. He created ever bigger ships&#8230;&#8221; (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói Brunel đã xây dựng đường sắt và sau đó xây dựng những con tàu khổng lồ, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">không nói ông thích (preferred) cái nào hơn</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. The Great Britain had more than one innovative feature.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;the first ocean-going steamship made of <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">iron</strong>, and the first to use the <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">underwater screw propeller</strong>&#8230;&#8221; (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Con tàu Great Britain có ít nhất hai đặc điểm đổi mới (innovative): làm bằng sắt (iron) và sử dụng chân vịt dưới nước (screw propeller) thay cho bánh guồng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. The design of the riverboat Archimedes was widely admired.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;only in 1838 did a large steamer use one, the riverboat Archimedes built by Francis Pettit Smith.&#8221; (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói tàu Archimedes là tàu lớn đầu tiên sử dụng chân vịt, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">không đề cập đến việc nó có được ngưỡng mộ rộng rãi hay không</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Modern ships that cross the Atlantic use the same energy source as the early steamships.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;In many modern ships, steam turbines have replaced engines with pistons, with <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">fuel oil instead of coal</strong> to fire the boilers.&#8221; (Đoạn cuối).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tàu hiện đại dùng dầu (fuel oil) hoặc diesel, trong khi tàu hơi nước đời đầu dùng than (coal). Đây là hai nguồn năng lượng khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
